<h3>Configuration Details</h3>

<p>
For Cisco routers, you will need something like the following example BGP configuration for peering LAN #1:
</p>

<pre>
    router bgp 64496

     ! {$options.identity.orgname} Peering LAN #1

     neighbor 185.6.36.6 remote-as 112
     neighbor 185.6.36.6 description {$options.identity.orgname} AS112 Service
     address-family ipv4
     neighbor 185.6.36.6 password s00persekr1t
     neighbor 185.6.36.6 activate
     neighbor 185.6.36.6 prefix-list pl-announce-to-inex out

</pre>

<p>
You should also use <code>route-maps</code> to control outgoing prefix
announcements to allow only the prefixes which you indend to announce.
</p>

